ap_2025_bark_penta: MEOWCH!? ("All wiped out!? Who's left to party in the mayhem?")
bark_briarvladimir_text_dialogone: Vladimir! Is this a... family meal?
bark_briarvladimir_text_dialogtwo: I should hope not. I wouldn't be caught dead at something so sentimental.
bark_cassiopeiakatarina_text_dialogone: Katarina, perhaps we should envenom your blades.
bark_cassiopeiakatarina_text_dialogtwo: They're deadly enough, in my hands.
bark_dariusdraven_text_dialogone: Brother. I hear you organized this whole Grand Reckoning for my homecoming.
bark_dariusdraven_text_dialogtwo: Whaaat? Me, giving you a spotlight 'cus I missed you or something? Nah. I'd never.
bark_dariustrundle_text_dialogone: You lost on home ground, Troll King. Now you find yourself in mine.
bark_dariustrundle_text_dialogtwo: Ugh. You and all these puny Noxians give me a headache.
bark_leblancelise_text_dialogone: Elise, what web do you weave over these Reckonings?
bark_leblancmordekaiser_text_dialogone: Revenant. The reviled... No. It must be a specter.
bark_leblancmordekaiser_text_dialogtwo: One who lives on, in the forsaken soul of every Reckoner.
bark_melleblanc_text_dialogone: Dark things roam every corner of Noxus, even here.
bark_melleblanc_text_dialogtwo: Gaze into the gloam, sister. Do you trust your eyes?
bark_sahnuzalmordekaiser_text_dialogone: A phantom enters my arena. What are you?
bark_sahnuzalmordekaiser_text_dialogtwo: A shade of a shade -- a warlord, ascended from wasted flesh.
bark_sionleblanc_text_dialogtwo: Be at peace, Sion. Let the roar of battle soothe you.
bark_swaindarius_text_dialogone: General Darius, the empire welcomes you home.
bark_swaindarius_text_dialogtwo: You honor me, Grand General. It's a relief to be back.
bark_taloncassiopeia_text_dialogone: Are you... Cassiopeia? Of Du Couteau?
bark_taloncassiopeia_text_dialogtwo: How honored the arena must feel, in the presence of such noble kin.
bark_vladimirswain_text_dialogone: Our dear Grand General graces us with his presence.
bark_vladimirswain_text_dialogtwo: Be advised, Lord Vladimir. Much as I'm watching the battles, I've an eye on you as well.

eliminationriskbark_text_alistar: @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@ should look out. Arena's hungry to see them slain.
eliminationriskbark_text_briar: Hey, @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@ are just holding back, right?
eliminationriskbark_text_darius: @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@ are on their last legs. But still they stand.
eliminationriskbark_text_draven: @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@ are almost out! Never heard that before.
eliminationriskbark_text_elise: @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@ are hurting dearly. But I'm not done with them yet.
eliminationriskbark_text_katarina: @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@ look rough. They need to steel themselves.
eliminationriskbark_text_kled: @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@ got nothin' left to lose, except their lives!
eliminationriskbark_text_leblanc: Do @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@ fear the dark? It inches ever closer...
eliminationriskbark_text_mel: As I once faced the most dire of moments, so must @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@.
eliminationriskbark_text_mordekaiser: Death has @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@ within grasp. Do they resist?
eliminationriskbark_text_rell: @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@ gotta get mean. It's do or die.
eliminationriskbark_text_riven: @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@ may fall soon, unless they fight back.
eliminationriskbark_text_sahnuzal: @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@ must prove worthy, or perish.
eliminationriskbark_text_samira: @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@ must like living on the edge, eh?
eliminationriskbark_text_swain: @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@ face death. Be wise, Reckoners.
eliminationriskbark_text_talon: @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@ need to sharpen up, or they're out.
eliminationriskbark_text_trundle: @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@ need to toughen up, or they dead meat.
eliminationriskbark_text_vladimir: @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@ must be careful. I'd hate to see them go.
eliminationriskbark_text_xinzhao: Death nears @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@. What must they sacrifice for victory?

feature_level_11_hardware_warning: <font color='#FF0000'>League is updating its DirectX usage soon. Your graphics card does not support DirectX feature level 11_0, you will need to upgrade your hardware so that you can continue playing after this upgrade.</font>
finalsbark_text_alistar: The Reckoners who remain... Brace yourselves for the last charge.
finalsbark_text_ambessa: Our last Grand Reckoners have made great sacrifices, and stand to make a few more…
finalsbark_text_briar: The final two teams! Savor this -- I know I will.
finalsbark_text_cassiopeia: Victory is in your clutches, my dears. Don't wither now.
finalsbark_text_darius: Only the strongest remain to do what must be done.
finalsbark_text_draven: A fight to the death between the top dogs? Draven approves.
finalsbark_text_elise: Only a few Reckoners are left. Who might be the last to feel my embrace?
finalsbark_text_katarina: Muster your courage, Reckoners. Your target's in reach.
finalsbark_text_kled: See these last fighters, Skaarl? that's what some courage looks like!
finalsbark_text_leblanc: After all the chaos has run its course, only the most cunning are left.
finalsbark_text_mel: Reckoners, allow the Fox and the Wolf to guide your final strikes.
finalsbark_text_mordekaiser: Of the souls who remain, only the mightiest shall earn a place in my ranks.
finalsbark_text_rell: This is the best out of the bunch? Alright, show me.
finalsbark_text_riven: The last two. The last stand.
finalsbark_text_sahnuzal: Hear the silence of the many fallen. Let it spur you forward.
finalsbark_text_samira: Ooh, the final challengers! Who's fearless enough to take it all?
finalsbark_text_swain: We near the end. Reckoners, harness your wisdom and strength of will.
finalsbark_text_talon: …You've made it this far, but don't let it get to your heads.
finalsbark_text_trundle: Don't care who wins. Just rip each other apart.
finalsbark_text_vladimir: Ah, we approach the last dance. Bittersweet, isn't it?
finalsbark_text_xinzhao: Surviving Reckoners, take heart -- as yours still beats.
firstplacebark_text_alistar: @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@ stand tall with a minotaur's strength.
firstplacebark_text_ambessa: @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@ have embodied tenets of the Medarda Code.
firstplacebark_text_briar: @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@ won! Bring out the feast! ...Wait, there's no food!?
firstplacebark_text_cassiopeia: @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@ endured above all. I'm charmed.
firstplacebark_text_darius: Noxus is emboldened by the power of @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@.
firstplacebark_text_draven: @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@, the ultimate Reckoners! Besides me.
firstplacebark_text_elise: @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@ have delivered a true feast for the eyes.
firstplacebark_text_katarina: No one left standing, no regrets. Good work, @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@.
firstplacebark_text_kled: I name @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@ Chief Sergeant Generals of the Grand Reckoning!
firstplacebark_text_leblanc: Intriguing, @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@. I may have plans for you...
firstplacebark_text_mordekaiser: @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@ served me... and will again, in eternity.
firstplacebark_text_rell: Horraaay, @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@... So happy for you.
firstplacebark_text_riven: Go, @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@. Find the triumph in victory that I couldn't.
firstplacebark_text_sahnuzal: @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@! Revel in your names, chanted across these lands!
firstplacebark_text_samira: Hah, @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@ made quite the reputation for themselves!
firstplacebark_text_talon: @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@ made their mark on the arena.
firstplacebark_text_trundle: Not bad, @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@. Go to the Freljord for real challenge.
firstplacebark_text_vladimir: Delicious, @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@! May their legacy live on...
firstplacebark_text_xinzhao: @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@. To be among the last standing... always I am humbled.

game_map_description_11: The newest and most venerated battleground is known as Summoner's Rift. Traverse down one of three different paths in order to attack your enemy at their weakest point. Work with your allies to siege the enemy base and destroy their Nexus!
game_map_description_12: The Howling Abyss is a bottomless crevasse located in the coldest, cruelest, part of the Freljord. Legends say that, long ago, a great battle took place here on the narrow bridge spanning this chasm. No one remembers who fought here, or why, but it is said that if you listen carefully to the wind you can still hear the cries of the vanquished tossed howling into the Abyss.
game_map_displaydescription_30: Queue up solo or partner with your friends in this multi-team game mode. Face against your foes in chaotic battles across diverse arenas.
game_map_mode_description_10_classic: Battle as a team of three to capture altars and siege the enemy nexus in this fast-paced game mode.
game_map_mode_description_11_arsr: Use a randomly selected champion to crush your lane, dive into epic five-on-five team fights, and destroy the enemy nexus.
game_map_mode_description_11_assassinate: Choose your favorite Assassin and hunt your way to victory in this Featured Game Mode.
game_map_mode_description_11_classic: Crush your lane, dive into epic five-on-five team fights, and destroy the enemy nexus in League's premier competitive mode.
game_map_mode_description_11_gamemodex: Venture to a long forgotten Ionian temple and destroy the enemy Nexus while completing a set of outrageous challenges—win the fight quickly, or the Nexus will do it for you!
game_map_mode_description_11_oneforall: Vote for and play five copies of the same champion! If no champion wins a strict majority, a random champion will be drawn from the pool of votes.
game_map_mode_description_11_practicetoo: Practice your favorite champion in this solo Summoner's Rift training gym.
game_map_mode_description_11_snowurf: A frigid fate awaits your foes! Fling spells and snowballs in this icy twist on ARURF, featuring League's coolest champions.
game_map_mode_description_11_urf: Fire off your abilities nonstop in this Ultra-Rapid game mode.
game_map_mode_description_12_aram: Ten randomly-selected champions assemble on a narrow bridge. Cross to the other side and destroy everything in your path.
game_map_mode_description_12_bilgewater: Ten randomly-selected champions battle over a narrow bridge in the heart of Bilgewater. Cross to the other side and destroy everything in your path.
game_map_mode_description_12_kingporo: Throw Poros at each other, summon the legendary Poro King, then feed him snax to push together to victory.
game_map_mode_description_12_portalparty: Portals have been unleashed upon the Howling Abyss! Ride them together as you push to victory.
game_map_mode_description_14_aram: Ten randomly-selected champions assemble on a narrow bridge in a frozen land. Cross to the other side and destroy everything in your path.
game_map_mode_description_16_darkstar: Play as Thresh and feed souls to the Dark Star to trigger the Singularity in this quick, round-based 3v3 mode set on the Cosmic Ruins.
game_map_mode_description_18_odyssey: Join the crew of the Morningstar on their search for Ora and Adventure in this 5-player co-op battle!
game_map_mode_description_18_starguardia: Fight together as Star Guardians against the invading monsters to save the city in this 5 player co-op battle!
game_map_mode_description_19_project: Stalk through the streets of PROJECT Substructure 43. Choose your Marksman, overcharge, and crush the opposing team. Now with Teemo Holograms.

hotstreakbark_text_alistar: Seems nothing can hold back @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@.
hotstreakbark_text_ambessa: @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@ prove... adequate, with their winning streak.
hotstreakbark_text_briar: Ooo, @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@ are killer killers! Wanna be friends?
hotstreakbark_text_darius: @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@ have gone on the offensive.
hotstreakbark_text_draven: @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@ are on fire! And... stealing my spotlight!
hotstreakbark_text_elise: With such wins, I feel @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@'s pulses rise.
hotstreakbark_text_katarina: @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@ push their lead. I like it.
hotstreakbark_text_kled: I see through my dumb eye that @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@ are winnin' big!
hotstreakbark_text_leblanc: A string of victories from @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@? I'm nearly surprised.
hotstreakbark_text_mel: Even I must commend the stubborn ingenuity of @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@.
hotstreakbark_text_rell: Hey @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@ are smashin' some heads.
hotstreakbark_text_sahnuzal: Behold, a series of victories from @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@.
hotstreakbark_text_samira: @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@ are going in with guns blazing!
hotstreakbark_text_swain: @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@ have momentum on their side.
hotstreakbark_text_trundle: @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@ fight with the hunger of trolls!
hotstreakbark_text_xinzhao: @PlayerAName@ and @PlayerBName@ have seen triumph after triumph.

introbark_text_alistar: Reckoners. No matter what you endure here, don't forget yourselves.
introbark_text_ambessa: Reckoners, the Medardas will not tolerate weakness.
introbark_text_briar: Huh, I haven't seen this side of Noxus before. It smells like... blood! And... guts!
introbark_text_cassiopeia: Oh, how the crowd howls and hisses. I'd hate for you to disappoint us.
introbark_text_elise: Grand Reckoners, may you weave and wend your way across the battlefield.
introbark_text_katarina: For Noxus' sake, never play it safe.
introbark_text_kled: Better not hold back now! I want you upstarts unruly and un-re-lenting!
introbark_text_leblanc: Worry not about me. Go on as if I'm not even here.
introbark_text_mel: I've yet to develop a taste for these… traditions. But the desire to prove oneself is admirable.
introbark_text_mordekaiser: This arena is an altar -- full to the brim with souls who will serve.
introbark_text_rell: Tch, Reckonings. 'Cus Noxians have nothing better to do than beat each other up.
introbark_text_riven: The Grand Reckoning. Back to all this bloodshed.
introbark_text_sahnuzal: To the death, tribespeople. You will crown me in carnage.
introbark_text_samira: The real show is here, you sorry lot. Now step up or shut up.
introbark_text_swain: Fellow Noxians, show me what minds and mettle you offer to our great empire.
introbark_text_talon: There are marks among the arena. If they aren't slain, I'll draw my blade.
introbark_text_trundle: This is no great troll hunt. Give me something to sink my teeth into!
introbark_text_vladimir: A generous invitation! I accept with a gift of my own -- @SubA@.
introbark_text_xinzhao: Fight with integrity, Reckoners, and you will not lose yourself to the arena.
jungle_focus_domination_description:
Passive - Gain Jungle Focus Domination
Your first basic attack on a monster below 50% health deals bonus magic damage equal to 6% of its maximum health. (Max: 300)
jungle_focus_resolve_description:
Passive - Gain Jungle Focus Resolve
Monsters that attack you take 2% of your total health as bonus magic damage.
jungle_focus_sorcery_description:
Passive - Gain Jungle Focus Sorcery
The first time your abilities deal damage to each monster, deal 6% of its current health as bonus magic damage. (Max: 300)

replayui_help_directedcamerabody:
Directed Camera [D]
Brings you to the action automatically.

Take temporary control by single clicking a champion or using the minimap.

Press Spacebar to see action elsewhere on the map.

Manual Camera [S]
Take full control of the camera at any time.

Lock on Champion [Double click a champion, double tap 1-5 or Q-T]
Focus on a champion to follow their movement.

replayui_help_timeshiftbody:
Timeline and Jump Back [Backspace]
Jump back to kills and other missed events.

Pause/play [P], Speed Up/Down [+/-], 1x Speed [0]
Control the game speed.

Jump to Furthest Viewed/Jump to Live [J]
Return to the furthest point you have seen.

teameliminatedbark_text_alistar: The arena has no respect for the slain. I do.
teameliminatedbark_text_ambessa: Reckoners have been felled. The Wolf will have its fill.
teameliminatedbark_text_atakhan: Wasted flesh, give in to me.
teameliminatedbark_text_briar: Oh, they're dead? Mmm, I'm feeling a tingling in my teeth...
teameliminatedbark_text_cassiopeia: Poor things. Succumbed to the throes of battle.
teameliminatedbark_text_darius: At least they died in competition, not cowardice.
teameliminatedbark_text_elise: How fortunate for those departed Reckoners... They've been caught in my web.
teameliminatedbark_text_katarina: A team's been cut down. Well, what else would they expect from a Reckoning?
teameliminatedbark_text_kled: Dang city folk. Serves 'em right -- don't know the first thing about real fightin'.
teameliminatedbark_text_leblanc: Another pair of Reckoners fades into obscurity...
teameliminatedbark_text_mel: As a Medarda, we move on from the fallen. As myself, I cannot help but feel...
teameliminatedbark_text_mordekaiser: Fallen. Frail. Unworthy... in this life.
teameliminatedbark_text_rell: Someone's down and out? Sucks for them.
teameliminatedbark_text_riven: The Reckoning pits have taken many... Too many.
teameliminatedbark_text_sahnuzal: If the gods will it, I shall meet the slain in the Hall of Bones.
teameliminatedbark_text_samira: Tapped out already? Tch, not worth my time.
teameliminatedbark_text_swain: A band of Reckoners have been eliminated. A shame.
teameliminatedbark_text_talon: Death is everywhere in Noxus. Alleyways, arenas... all the same.
teameliminatedbark_text_vladimir: Goodbye, adorable little things. The pleasure was all mine.
teameliminatedbark_text_xinzhao: May the fallen find peace. They were warriors, all.
tips_sample:
This is a sample tips string.
And I can have multiple lines of texts.
This is a new line.
tips_sample2:
In case you don't know, tips are randomly chosen
from a huge list.
tips_sample3:
We may need to have a backdrop for tips area,
so it's aesthetically better, and easier to
make sure the texts fits inside the intended area.
uniquebark_text_alistar: You may be down, but you're not out.
uniquebark_text_ambessa: A bold maneuver. Fight readily, without fear or hesitation.
uniquebark_text_ambessareward: Your pledge has paid off. For your efforts, you are rewarded.
uniquebark_text_briar: That's right cut loose, claw your way back!
uniquebark_text_kled: Hey, yer fight's over --  cast that Interference into any ongoing battles!
uniquebark_text_swain: Be rewarded for clever tactics and strategies.
vanguard_dialog_cheaterdetected: You have been detected as using cheats and have been kicked from the game.
vanguard_gameendexplanation: A cheater has been detected and your game has been terminated. No win or loss has been credited to any player.
voicechatpanel_message_connecttouse: Connect to use League Voice with your party!
voicechatpanel_message_emptychannel: No one else in your party is currently connected to League Voice!
voicechatpanel_message_voiceunavailable: Sorry, League Voice is currently unavailable.
voteenterbark_text_alistar: I know this arena well. Here, I've been beat down, but I always stand back up.
voteenterbark_text_ambessa: Battle demands sacrifice. This, I will make sure you learn -- and learn well.
voteenterbark_text_briar: Hi! I'm Briar, and I'm starving -- kinda running on empty. But that's when meals taste best...
voteenterbark_text_cassiopeia: Giving me your heart? You must like the rush coursing through your veins...
voteenterbark_text_darius: I am back, Noxus. I've seen that it is through hardship we are stronger.
voteenterbark_text_draven: There's one right choice. You want power and glory? Draven's got it.
voteenterbark_text_elise: You look scared stiff, Reckoner. Come closer -- I won't bite.
voteenterbark_text_katarina: Taking a chance on me? You're a daring one, Reckoner.
voteenterbark_text_kled: It's not foul play I got on offer, but pure, unadulterated chaos.
voteenterbark_text_leblanc: Tell me, Reckoner -- how do you face the unknown? The unseen?
voteenterbark_text_mel: A... strained homecoming this is, but I will show Noxus the worth of my travels.
voteenterbark_text_mordekaiser: Reckoner. I promise eternity -- a realm beyond mortal ken.
voteenterbark_text_rell: Name's Rell. Looking to get all the shiny stuff? I can help... if you're not an idiot.
voteenterbark_text_riven: Reckoning has some brutal rules... I stand against them.
voteenterbark_text_sahnuzal: Warrior, you will have only one chance to prove your mettle to me.
voteenterbark_text_samira: Of course you're choosing me. I like the ones who shoot first.
voteenterbark_text_swain: A word of advice, Reckoner -- survey the battlefield before you strike.
voteenterbark_text_talon: This place is full of contracts to claim. Let me show you.
voteenterbark_text_trundle: I want to see you fight with all you have! Teeth, claws, clubs -- doesn't matter!
voteenterbark_text_vladimir: Hello, Reckoner. I've a humble triubute to give all of you, if you'll have me.
voteenterbark_text_xinzhao: The arena demands much from you. If chosen, I will provide what respite I can.

Seems like my last Squad-mail pep talk paid off. That last mission of yours was impressive. I haven't seen someone improve so drastically since… well me, probably.

Your Fellow Battle Bat,
V

S: So!
I: …

I: I will not lie, little leader… that was impressive.
L: I didn't think someone who uses their legs so little could kick so much ***.
S: I knew all you needed was to see me out in the field!
S: So when do we meet up for workout time?
I: Whoa, slow down. We didn't say you were invited yet.
S: But I probably obliterated a thousand grunts, just on my own!
S: Didn't you see me “pew pew?” So fast and furiously?!
I: No, we saw. I don't think I'll ever unsee.
L: Our training also takes discipline. You'd have to agree to some terms.
S: I can do that! I'm agreeable.
I: Repeat after me:
I: As a member of the “Secret Gym Club,” I swear to uphold the sanctity of our very serious order…
S: As a member of the “Secret Gym Club,” I swear to uphold the sanctity of our very serious order…
I: To grind until I break my records…
S: To grind until I break my records…
I: To lift double my weight…
S: To lift double my weight…
I: And to always spot for my squad.
S: And to always spot for my squad.
L: That's it.
S: That's it? I can join the secret gym sesh?
L: Yeah. You proved yourself. Plus… you're good company.
I: Welcome aboard, little leader.
S: YAY! I swear I won't tell anybody.
S: Also, I have the PERFECT workout playlist.

{095ee2b173}:
Final City!

Your “Anima Squad” is divided and broken. They, too, harbor a traitor, a member of my legion too weak to face the glory of our ascension! Unwittingly, she lured your so-called heroes into a trap. And now they lead her back to you, and still your faith remains? This is the lunacy of your species—your sense of mercy. But I have none.

At this moment, your “saviors” traverse a hidden underground home of your progenitors. There, they have discovered what I broadcast to you now: there is no guiltlessness in war! This world was ravaged, its rivers sucked dry, its forests purged, its sun blotted out. Not by my legion, but by primitive “curiosity,” the bane of your people! We Primordians seek only recompense!

Your pup, the swordsman, discovered this truth and abandoned you! He runs back now, tail between his legs. His reunion will be brief, for my hordes are pounding at your door!

No bastion will protect you! Hide! Cower! We will pluck you from your high-rises and Anima Squad will watch, helpless, as we drink deeply of your gore!

Cherish your final moments, Final City. Extinction has arrived!

{0e8c8b536f}:
Xayah,

Saw your performance in that battle today via Bat-Drone. I'd apologize for the intrusion of your privacy, but I know you'd do the same. (If not, you wouldn't really be a Battle Bat worth your weight in squid salt.)

Quick pointer: stop leaving those feather blades of yours all over the place. They make a trail that could lead directly back to you… and they're a pain to clean up. Squad Maintenance has a long message thread going for how many they've had to pick up off the battlefield. And believe me, you don't want to annoy the people that pick up after us. Made that mistake once, and came home to my door “decorated” with arrows.

Taught me that Anima Squad can't afford to be sloppy. We need to be efficient and precise to avoid close calls. I think you can do it. I see a lot of myself in you. A younger, brasher, somewhat-less-skilled self... but you get the point.

Keep fighting. I'll be watching.
V

{0f3c835e48}:
Filed under Mission Code A.W.O.F

Saw the Old Wolf again. His patterns are predictable. He rises out of the abandoned laboratory as the sun kisses the horizon, and dips back below (bag full, likely of discovered rations) before the heat of day. He does not think he is being watched, or does not care. He moves gracefully, yet his steps are heavy, as if he is burdened by some invisible weight.

The new wolf, Sylas, is without a leader, without one to guide him on his path. He hides his disappointment well, fearing that he too may be sent on some mission and told to never return. It is one thing to be lonely among many, and another thing entirely to truly be alone.

There are times when I feel the Old Wolf turn his sights to me. He looks not into our hidden cameras, but through. We share this moment, our eyes locked onto one another, each picturing the other at our side. Like the moments we used to share as children, training, locked in a duel with wooden swords. Dreaming of the day when we would join Anima Squad together.

But it was always just that—a dream.

L: Hi Yuumi, I need help deciding on a weapon for an upcoming mission.
Y: I can help with that!
J: Oooh! AI! I love this stuff. So easy to break by asking random questions!
Y: Do you have a question for me?
L: No, she does not. Unless it relates to weapon efficiency.
J: What's your favorite food?
Y: Sorry, I can't consume nutrients.
J: Aww, that is so sad.
L: Jinx, just let the AI process my question.
Y: Do you have a question for me?
L: Yes, I already asked it.
Y: Yes. I see now. You asked, “What's your favorite food?”
Y: I answered, “I can't consume nutrients.”
Y: Would you like to know more?
J: Yes please, tell us more about food, cat-bot!
Y: Food is defined as a nutritious substance that lifeforms eat to maintain life.
L: Yuumi, reset.
Y: What is… life?

Seraphine:

Forwarding you one of Riven's battle transcripts, per your request. The last one we have recorded. Maybe you can find some comfort in reading it.

MF


BATTLE BAT DRONE RECORDING 76X72BLM21
DATE: REDACTED

COMMANDER: Fall back!
*screeching cries*
*bleating*
UNIDENTIFIED SQUAD MEMBER: We've lost the forward defenses, Commander.
COMMANDER: Thanks— *bzzt* — tell Officer — *bzzt* secure the western perimeter.
USM: We've lost contact with her battalion.
COMMANDER: Then we— LOOK OUT!
*squelching*
*clinking weapons*
USM: I—thank you Commander. I didn't see them coming… I—
COMMANDER: You would have done the same. You ALL would have.
*silence*
*distant gunfire*
COMMANDER: Listen up! I know it may look bleak. I know that forward progress feels like a broken promise! But the people we're fighting for… they still believe.
USM: But what if our fight isn't enough?
*indiscernible whispering*
COMMANDER: Then we'll find another way. We'll take the battle to them. We won't give up. Hoping in the face of hopelessness makes us human. That's—
USM: Commander. The western perimeter has been breached.
COMMANDER: Watch each others' backs. FOR FINAL CITY!
*chittering*
*screams*

{17bc2d8dcf}:
Followed Commander Fortune's orders exactly as she laid them out:
 Meet up with your new squad.
 Push back the horde.
 Head to the source of Riven's signal.
 No singing.
… Okay, so I broke one rule. But I couldn't resist singing a totally kick-butt anthem just as I was, well, kicking butt!
My new squad is WAY different from my former desk buddies, all “reloading!” this and “bogey on my six!” that.
Illaoi probably has the biggest muscles I've ever seen. She says she could bench press a Crusher, and you know what? I totally believe her.
Didn't get to talk to Xayah much. She grabbed my coordinates and ran off, muttering something about “scouting things out for the newbie.” Typical Battle Bat, so secretive!
Leona probably saved my skin a dozen times in just our first battle! She also packed our meals from the trip, so I guess she's saving my stomach too!
There's no fiercer fighter than Jinx—I've watched the highlight reels with Riven, so I know it when I see it—but she might enjoy war a bit too much.
Goes without saying (but I probably should, because this is a mission report and all) that we showed those Primordians a thing or two. Even that giant one tunneling all over the city!
We've started our journey to the signal's source. I know the path ahead is dangerous, but with my squad by my side, anything is possible!
Ooh, I feel a new song coming on…!

A: Briar, do you have more time to chat?
B: Sure do! Just finished dinner number two, so I gotta rest my stomach for a second!
A: Great, I'd love to learn more about Primordian culture. We discussed cuisine before. Which was interesting but… inconclusive.
B: I got you, Aurora! Being a Primordian is about way more than just eating. We have a rich culture of, um…
B: Well, I can't think of anything else other than food. Could you give me a point in the right direction?
A: Do Primordians swim as their primary form of transportation? Or do you utilize others?
B: Interesting question!
A: You don't know the answer, do you?
B: Well I swim. And walk on land. The feeling of your feet walking through grass… unbeatable! Except maybe by the feeling of feet on cool wood flooring. Or food in your mouth!
A: Have you ever witnessed a Primordian not swim? We've marked the speeds in which Primordians travel underwater. Faster than any of our submarines.
B: Guess we just evolved that way. All the tech we built was to enhance ourselves, sort of like an extension of our bodies. So all the Primordians I know swim everywhere they go.
A: Fascinating. Still… you are slower on land. Perhaps a wheeled shoe would be suitable?
B: Wheels? Those little rounded thingies that taste all bitter and fizzle when you bite 'em?
A: Have you… eaten tires before?
B: Maybe. But I never get tired of eating!! Heh. Heh.

J: Yep! Commence!

{204462954e}:
B: You HAVE to tell me about that hat, Aurora. It's so BIG AND POINTY!
A: It's much more than just a hat. It's also a supercomputer. I prefer fashion that is functional.
B: Me too! Or… well, I would. If I knew anything about fashion. My only opinion: I HATE SHOES.
A: I, too, hate shoes. But they serve an important function: protecting our feet from the elements as well as harmful bacteria. Hiking shoes, for instance, keep you from stepping on sharp rocks.
B: What's hiking?
A: It's like walking. With a purpose. Upwards.
B: Anima Squad really has names for every kinda walking, huh?
A: It's my favorite physical activity. One of the few I can do on my own.
B: Oh! Like mandatory sporting outings! Watching the teams fight over the sphere!
A: Yeah, I don't really understand all that either.
B: You don't need to understand. You just cheer! And eat! And stand when they play the sing-a-long song!
A: Yeah… I'd prefer not to.
B: You don't like the sing-a-long song?
A: No, I don't like the… people. The song is fine. But I prefer other types of music.
B: Like Seraphine's songs?
A: No comment.
B: Her music is like a worm that gets in your ear and you just can't get it out! Do you have a word for that?
A: Earworm.
B: No, that's what I said. A different word.
A: The word is “earworm.”
B: Humans are weird.

{22be46fd97}:
My squad is the greatest!

Leona convinced me that I had this important task at HQ. Something super bureaucratic, filing paperwork, interviews, I don't remember. I sort of zoned out when she was explaining it because it sounded so boring.

Luckily, it was all a lie! She leads me into this office room with all the lights off, and when I flip the switch, my whole squad is standing there, shouting “Surprise!” I screamed a little bit—but I definitely wasn't scared. They decorated the place with confetti (Briar shredded the paper herself), a piñata (that Briar had already destroyed, but it's the thought that counts), and balloons (Briar drew shark faces on them, which was a nice touch).

Leona then had everyone give me gifts. They were so sweet! I swear that deep down, Xayah is a big softie. I saw her crack a smile when I said I loved the watch she got me! Illaoi already showed me how to listen to her music recording on one of those archived tape players. And Aurora's owl is ADORABLE. I have the perfect spot for it on my desk.

Easily the best part of the night was when Illaoi whipped out the karaoke machine. That's the marker of the perfect party: a big singalong with all your friends.

Seraphine, signing off.

{2648e2fe4b}:
S: Commander, thanks so much for sending me that classified recording! I won't mention it by name here, because I know this isn't a secure channel!
MF: Seraphine, I'm the head of Anima Squad. You don't have to worry about getting reprimanded. There's no one to report this to. Our org doesn't go any higher.
S: Oh! Of course.
MF: So. What did you think?
S: What did I think? I mean, so much!
S: I know some people think that Riven just abandoned us, but this has to prove that she would never do that, right?
S: The way she talks about Final City… it doesn't sound like… I mean… What do you think, Commander?
MF: Ha! Well if I were more like Riven, I'd say a commander doesn't think… they do.
MF: But I'm not the same leader that she was. Riven inspired her people, but she didn't talk to them. I'm not sure we'll ever know how she really felt.
MF: You don't have anything to say?
S: No, I'm just suppressing it! I'm so happy you're finally opening up to me!
MF: Don't make me regret it.
S: I won't, I won't!
MF: I've pored over all of Riven's logs, ones with much higher security clearance, and I don't feel any closer to her. Or understand why she'd leave.
S: Maybe she found another way. Maybe… she didn't. But I trust you to lead us. Riven may have been the first, but you're my Commander.
MF: Thanks Seraphine. And… let's keep this off the record.

{2984aed279}:
The last 24 hours have been an experience that I would not wish upon even the strongest of my squad. The citizens I came here to rescue quiver in my haphazard shelter, eyes betraying a fear that will take years of counseling to suppress.

First, there were the storms. I will never again doubt Final City's automated climate system. We were bombarded with rain that never ceased, waves that dwarfed the trees. (I pray that HQ sends towels with the rescue chopper.)

Luckily, I recalled a story about crafting a hut of mud and branches, of which there were plenty. The heroes of the tale did not have to deal with these elements. There was a bear and a strange, intangible monster in their woods, though, so I am thankful for the rain instead.

At 1900 hours, I thought I heard a beast beyond the treeline, but it was just my stomach growling. I soon found myself wading in shallow waves, dunking my hand below to grab a fish searching for sand scum or low-floating kelp. Found a few. The rain made cooking impossible. Sashimi would have to suffice.

Daybreak was a blessing. The sound of birds chirping was interrupted by the chirping of my communication device: rescue was inbound. When my feet met hardened concrete in the boundaries of Final City's walls, I swore that I would never greet the sand again…

Until the next mission calls for it. The things I do for my people.

{2a05761c0b}:
Mission Code: Alpha Whiskey Oscar Foxtrot.

It's been six solar cycles since my last official contact with Final City. My only correspondence is these “reports,” to which I get no reply. I have no way of knowing whether or not they are read or forgotten, printed and folded into paper cranes for recycled decoration.

I was told my mission was of grave importance, but Riven is either a liar or a fool. She said “to search for a weapon capable of destroying the Primordians once and for all.” How quickly my task led to disillusion. There is no end to these monsters' resources, no hidden weakness, no glowing red spot sheathed beneath armored plating.

Home feels like a dream now, one which even sleep never brings. I was told to put the mission above all else, that watching Anima from afar would only twist the knife deeper. I saw each of our names fade from the team's lips, as new blood rose to take our places. But there is no turning back.

Sylas is like me. He bears the mark of a man untrusting, uncompromising. I hope that he does not drop his guard.

There is another still, one I can only watch as he lives his life without me. I dare not write his name. I wait underground, amongst the creations of humanity long ago, for a day when courage steels me. Wait. And watch. And hope.

{33ef97e092}:
Hello all you beautiful people!

Battle Dove Seraphine, here, stealing the mic from Commander Fortune to give you an Anima-Update…

We did it! I won't lie to you, it was looking pretty bad for a second, but it's in our darkest moments that we shine the brightest!

I have to give a special shout-out to my squad for trusting me. Look at what we accomplished together! Defeating a skyscraper-sized Primordian leading a full-scale invasion of the city? Even Riven didn't do that!

Yasuo, thank you for guiding me and the team back home. I know things are different now… but I really hope you decide to stick around. Anima Squad needs you.

Illaoi, Xayah, and Leona! Without their strength and wisdom, I wouldn't be half the “little leader” I am!

To our newest teammate Briar, I speak for everyone when I say YOU'RE SO AWESOME. And if you think I don't speak for you… then I'll send my friend Jinx to make you agree.

Just kidding. Jinx!? Jinx, come back here!

…I should probably go make sure she doesn't actually hurt anybody.

*bzztt* Final City, this is Commander Fortune. Seraphine is right… though I might've worded things a bit differently. We've won a long and hard-fought battle.

The war isn't over. The Primordians are still out there, and so is Aatrox. But we're stronger now. More knowledgeable. And we've got a “Briar.”

When they come back, we'll be ready.

L: Jinx, I need your opinion on the most efficient weapon for an upcoming mission.
J: Hey Le-Le. Hm, don't love that nickname. Maybe Leo? Leoness. Like a Lioness?
L: Just Leona is fine. Did you get my message about the weapon?
J: Sorry, I can't just call you Leona! All my friends get nicknames!
L: I was thinking maybe bringing a Radiant Field with me. But you're the weapon expert.
J: I'm also a nickname expert. Did you know that I call Commander Fortune just plain ol' “Fortune”?
L: Everyone does that.
J: Wait, what?! Ugh. Must've copied me.
L: There's sure to be a lot of Primordian resistance, so maybe The Annihilator?
J: Y'know, “The Annihilator” isn't a bad nickname for you. Though usually nicknames are shorter than real names.
L: I'm talking about a weapon. For a mission. Not my nickname.
J: Oh wow, so you just want to totally derail our nicknaming conversation?
L: …

{3d7fc4f4ee}:
I have found myself in a predicament. This was meant to be a simple search and rescue: two citizens stranded on a nearby island after a failed romantic tryst. Now I am stranded with them.

The coordinates were accurate. I discovered the island without any issue. It's small, light on vegetation, and practically absent of any fauna. The library holds records of densely populated islets rich in biodiversity, where the animals that are many of my squad members' namesakes would exist in relative harmony. But this place is a wasteland. Hard to see signs of romance amongst the unyielding sand.

The citizens were scared, certainly. A Primordian had sunk their stolen ship. They begged and swore they would never leave the boundaries of Final City again. I laughed. I was not sent to administer justice. (Though if I was, I would not let them off so easily.)

As we approached my vehicle, a swarm of tentacles (each as large as myself) rose from the waters. I rushed to repel them, but was not quick enough. It was… regrettable.

The area is clearly compromised. Sending another squad ship would be dangerous… or worse, pointless. Extraction by air is our only option. Resources are limited. HQ estimates that we will need to wait 24 hours.

I have read many stories of brave adventurers cast off to sea. Trapped on islands with pigs, other seamen, and sports paraphernalia. They survived in the harshest of environments. I will do the same… I must.
